detaileddescription.para:
Normal usage in Gromacs command-line programs is like this: intmain(intargc,char*argv[])
{
gmx::init(&argc,&argv);
try
{
//Theactualcodefortheprogram
return0;
}
catch(conststd::exception&ex)
{
gmx::printFatalErrorMessage(stderr,ex);
returngmx::processExceptionAtExit(ex);
}
}

Basic usage: if(value<0)
{
GMX_THROW(InconsistentUserInput("Negativevaluesnotallowedforvalue"));
}

Typical usage (note that gmx::File wraps this particular case): FILE*fp=fopen("filename.txt","r");
if(fp==NULL)
{
GMX_THROW(FileIOError("Couldnotopenfile"),"fopen",errno);
}

Usage: try
{
//C++code
}
GMX_CATCH_ALL_AND_EXIT_WITH_FATAL_ERROR;
